Quote
|You've done it, then! Defeated Halsaime, broken his curse! What a fine song that will make by a tavern fire! The Song of Druid's Deep, I'll call it!
|Tarim
}}
The song was created to commemorate the events that occurred around the [[Druid's Deep]] of [[Thorngap]], in the [[King's Forest]] of [[Cormyr]], which was taken over by the [[druid]] [[Halsaime]] after he was corrupted and maddened by [[Halsaime's staff|a cursed staff]]. Although he caused a great deal of destruction and suffering as he plotted to conquer the world, Tarim, [[Jussko Kwahn]], [[Kirinel Zay]], and some heroic [[adventurer]]s managed to stop him and destroy the staff before he could do more than threaten [[Eveningstar]].

